## Objective
Make the TS particles background way more stylized:
- Using gradients (color stops in ctx or css).
- Animation noisiness using svg stuff (perhaps draw with SVG-like paths, or use SVG noise filter if overlay, but since canvas, simulate Perlin with math or simple noise func for jitter).
- Like a sea of Perlin noise well distributed (add layered noise for organic flow, multiple particle types with different noise offsets, distribute evenly but organic, slow drifting waves).

Likely target: FrutigerScenes canvas particles (already has ~92 particles, hearts/sparks/dots, connect lines, mouse attract, girly colors). Enhance the draw/animate for more stylized sea-like noise.

Keep performance (cap count), mobile touch.

## Constraints / Invariants
- Preserve audio handoff, time gates, scene logic, orchid end.
- IIPS, elegant.
- Well distributed, no clustering.
- Use existing colors (aero-pink etc) + gradients.

## Verification
- Particles look like stylized Perlin sea (organic, noisy, gradient fills, animated jitter).
- No perf drop, build clean.
- In gift scene bg.
